  • ISO 100 6400 (expandable to H: 12800) for shooting from bright light to low light compatible with eye Fi cards Multimedia cards (MMC) cannot be used

Looking for specific info?

From the manufacturer

Share Photos that Impress

The EOS Rebel T6 camera can be ideal for anyone looking to step up their imaging game. Equipped with an 18.0 Megapixel CMOS image sensor and many automatic and creative options, the EOS Rebel T6 is easy to use, simple to share wirelessly with and delivers impressive image quality to your audience.

Previous page

  1. High Detail, High Quality

    Brilliantly clear and colorful images are at hand with the 18.0 Megapixel (APS-C) CMOS sensor and powerful DIGIC 4+ Image Processor, even in low light thanks to the cameras wide ISO of 1006400.

Next page
Wireless Connectivity

Wireless Possibilities

Built-in Wi-Fi* and NFC** capability allows for easy uploading to social media sites, remote shooting through the free Canon Camera Connect app*, image transfer to compatible devices and more.

Previous page

  1. AF Performance

    Accurate Viewfinder

    The Optical Viewfinder allows quick, accurate focusing by firmly framing and capturing your subject.

  2. AF Performance

    9-point AF System

    The EOS Rebel T6's 9-point AF system with a center cross-type AF can deliver fast and precise focus.

  3. AF Performance

    Continuous Shooting

    The EOS Rebel T6 captures up to 3.0 fps (frames per second), fast enough to capture action shots.

Next page
1 Optical Viewfinder 2 9-point AF System 3 Continuous Shooting
Full HD Video

Full HD Made Easy and Bright

Record Full HD video with superb quality and beautiful background blur, even under low-light conditions. The EOS Rebel T6 is compatible with all EF/EF-S lenses to help you realize the movie director in you. Try different lenses for fun and new perspectives.

Previous page

  1. Creative Operation

    Mode Dial

    For more creative shooting, simply twist the Mode Dial to try out modes like Portrait and Landscape.

  2. Creative Operation

    Scene Intelligent Auto

    The EOS Rebel T6's Scene Intelligent Auto mode helps deliver beautiful and accurate exposure.

  3. Creative Operation

    Basic+ Mode

    With Basic+, select image effects like Warm, Vivid, Monochrome and more on the Quick Control Screen.

Next page
1 Mode Dial 2 Scene Intelligent Auto 3 Basic+ Mode

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Feature guide

    LCD monitor

As I became more familiar with the various ISO, F/S, and shutter speed settings, I switched up to shooting using the eye piece and used the display to quickly see/adjust my manual settings.

    Picture quality
    I'm pretty impressed. The pictures come out clear and sharp (assuming its correctly focused when on manual focus). The colors are bold and vibrant in my opinion. I don't think the pictures of my kids have ever turned out so good. Side note: I did start using the auto focus feature recently while on a road trip to be able to shoot faster and I am very please with how well the pictures turned out. It was quick to focus and will likely be using this feature often when I am out and about (with little time to set up the shot).

    I am incredibly happy with my purchase and if I had to do over again, I would pick this model. After purchasing this camera, I purchased a used Canon 30D for my son as he wanted to learn as well. In comparison, the Canon EOS has come a long way in terms of design, ease of use for a beginner, and features but if anything, I know based on having both a new and used (old) camera in the house now, that they can stand the test of time if cared for properly.     Perfect intro level DSLR. Plenty of awesome source material out there to get going and get shooting. You could have the most expensive, mirrorless, digital, precision wrought camera in all the world that would still take shoddy photos if ones skill level was low. This camera is a perfect entry level to stepping up your game as a serious photog, as a youtube content creator and a plethora of other creative endeavours. If you're new to this type of camera set up the initial learning curve might feel a bit tough but its very adaptive and super easy to navigate once you do. One piece of advice would be this: buy and extra battery so you always have one on charge ready to pop since waiting around for a single rechargeable power pack to be ready will totally wreck your stride and other field testing, it sucks to have to cut short a really good project simply because you ran out of juice.
